312
00:26:41,882 --> 00:26:43,234
So how's the family?

313
00:26:43,354 --> 00:26:46,231
Daniel's fine. But Jen.

314
00:26:46,423 --> 00:26:47,861
That's another story.

315
00:26:47,957 --> 00:26:50,642
Yeah, I really like her. I mean,
how could you fuck that up?

316
00:26:50,834 --> 00:26:52,728
Well, it wasn't hard.

317
00:26:52,962 --> 00:26:55,725
By the way, thanks for that out there.

318
00:26:55,956 --> 00:26:56,756
Made me look good.

319
00:26:56,876 --> 00:26:59,274
Well, hope it helps.

320
00:26:59,369 --> 00:27:00,520
Yeah, well, the people I'm tracking,

321
00:27:00,616 --> 00:27:03,206
they expect the FBI
to pay me some visits like this.

322
00:27:03,301 --> 00:27:04,451
Makes me look legit.

323
00:27:04,571 --> 00:27:06,179
Was that in the Interpol handbook?

324
00:27:06,370 --> 00:27:09,823
Come on, John, there no science
to catching crooks you know that.

325
00:27:10,015 --> 00:27:11,429
Yeah. You said
you had something for me.

326
00:27:11,549 --> 00:27:12,412
Yeah.

327
00:27:15,193 --> 00:27:16,632
Our friend over in Brussels,

328
00:27:16,824 --> 00:27:19,221
the guy that makes
those titanium bullets

329
00:27:20,852 --> 00:27:22,746
found him two days ago.

330
00:27:22,866 --> 00:27:23,729
Then I ran a check.

331
00:27:23,825 --> 00:27:27,757
It seems everyone associated
with Rogue is having some bad luck.

332
00:27:30,592 --> 00:27:31,952
Just last week...

333
00:27:32,072 --> 00:27:34,828
plastic surgeon down in Panama
accidentally impaled himself...

334
00:27:34,948 --> 00:27:37,922
with a kitchen knife
making a turkey sandwich.

335
00:27:38,042 --> 00:27:41,063
Week before that another one of our
scalpel friends down in Florida

336
00:27:41,183 --> 00:27:43,844
went skinny-dipping with some gators.

337
00:27:43,964 --> 00:27:47,896
Guess he didn't read the signs. Anyway.

338
00:27:48,016 --> 00:27:52,499
These guys, they both
specialize in facial reconstruction.

339
00:27:52,787 --> 00:27:54,034
Both of them.

340
00:27:56,125 --> 00:27:57,846
Our man's tying up loose ends.

341
00:27:57,966 --> 00:28:00,364
Yeah, well there's another surgeon
unaccounted for.

342
00:28:00,459 --> 00:28:03,336
Think he might be still alive,
maybe hiding out.

343
00:28:03,456 --> 00:28:05,878
You let me know
the second he surfaces.

344
00:28:05,998 --> 00:28:07,460
Right. Thanks Benny.

345
00:28:16,571 --> 00:28:18,777
Button up, this isn't a disco.

346
00:28:22,613 --> 00:28:23,860
Is that our contact?

347
00:28:25,490 --> 00:28:27,024
Yes my contact.

348
00:28:32,299 --> 00:28:34,025
Get rid of him.

349
00:28:34,145 --> 00:28:35,632
He's my brother. He's with me.

350
00:28:35,752 --> 00:28:37,861
Who the fuck does this guy think he is?

351
00:28:42,561 --> 00:28:43,807
Go back to your car.

352
00:28:43,903 --> 00:28:46,205
Wu, please. He's an outsider.

353
00:28:46,325 --> 00:28:48,794
Go! Don't make me say it again.

354
00:29:00,015 --> 00:29:02,508
After this is done
you and I are going to talk.

355
00:29:10,715 --> 00:29:14,784
The Horses are intact.
Shiro will be pleased.

356
00:29:14,976 --> 00:29:17,949
We will contact you when we get there.

357
00:29:29,265 --> 00:29:31,663
Are the Horses safe with this crew?

358
00:29:31,759 --> 00:29:34,732
Of, course, as far as they know
they're just delivering cars.

359
00:30:15,299 --> 00:30:16,929
Stay calm and cooperate.

360
00:30:17,025 --> 00:30:19,039
It's just a routine check.

361
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:26,880
I need you out of the car, both of you.

362
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,533
Put your hands where I can see them.

363
00:30:28,653 --> 00:30:31,122
Officer, we're with
Shiro Yanagawa Enterprises.

364
00:30:31,218 --> 00:30:32,464
You are making a huge mistake.

365
00:30:32,465 --> 00:30:33,520
We have made arrangements.

366
00:30:33,616 --> 00:30:34,863
Out of the car!

367
00:30:42,535 --> 00:30:44,069
Do it. Turn around.

368
00:30:46,275 --> 00:30:47,905
We work security.

369
00:30:48,001 --> 00:30:50,495
We have licenses to carry firearms.
Call your Captain.

370
00:30:50,591 --> 00:30:53,180
- Shut up. Shut up.
- He'll vouch for us.

371
00:30:55,386 --> 00:30:57,112
- Fucking rent a cops.
- Shut up.

372
00:31:02,377 --> 00:31:03,121
Good evening.

373
00:31:03,241 --> 00:31:06,127
Captain Andrews,
what the fuck is going on?

374
00:31:06,223 --> 00:31:08,322
What about our arrangement?

375
00:31:08,442 --> 00:31:13,320
Just a little change in plan.
I need my money. Now.

376
00:31:23,965 --> 00:31:26,554
So, we are good to go?

377
00:31:26,746 --> 00:31:28,952
Oh, yeah. You're good to go.

378
00:31:29,048 --> 00:31:33,172
Just wait here for a sec.
Let me and the boys clear out.

379
00:31:33,267 --> 00:31:34,035
Let's go.

380
00:31:34,802 --> 00:31:35,569
Do it.

381
00:31:36,912 --> 00:31:38,830
Mr. Chang sends his regards.

382
00:31:38,926 --> 00:31:39,981
No-o-o!

383
00:31:57,723 --> 00:32:00,887
CHANG'S WAREHOUSE 16

384
00:32:42,893 --> 00:32:44,907
Compliments of Mr. Chang.

385
00:33:20,199 --> 00:33:22,788
Some serious shit here, brother.

386
00:33:22,884 --> 00:33:25,378
Yakuzas. All of them.

387
00:33:25,474 --> 00:33:29,406
All lined up, shot through the back.
Execution-style.

388
00:33:29,597 --> 00:33:33,625
Excuse me, Forensics wants to know if
you're ready for them to come in yet.

389
00:33:40,914 --> 00:33:42,448
It was a heist.

390
00:33:42,725 --> 00:33:43,551
What?

391
00:33:44,654 --> 00:33:47,339
Check the space between these sedans.

392
00:33:48,874 --> 00:33:50,888
These guys were
escorting something big.

393
00:33:51,008 --> 00:33:53,477
Whatever it was,
it must have been important.

394
00:33:56,642 --> 00:33:59,423
These guys were the guard dogs.

395
00:33:59,519 --> 00:34:01,629
But they left their guns in the cars.

396
00:34:01,725 --> 00:34:05,753
There's only one thing that would stop
these guys from throwing down.

397
00:34:05,944 --> 00:34:07,766
Cops.

398
00:34:07,767 --> 00:34:10,068
At least they thought they were cops.

399
00:34:10,164 --> 00:34:13,617
Hold on just a damn minute. Are you
trying to say that cops did this?

400
00:34:15,535 --> 00:34:17,045
If they didn't, they were involved.

401
00:34:17,165 --> 00:34:18,987
No fucking way!

402
00:34:19,083 --> 00:34:21,577
For all we know
it could have been one of you guys.

403
00:35:03,486 --> 00:35:07,514
I'm assuming that
you know who the fuck I am.

404
00:35:07,706 --> 00:35:10,775
You're a bitch for Shiro Yanagawa
aren't you, Captain?

405
00:35:11,150 --> 00:35:15,186
You're the one who gives his boys
free passage to smuggle in shit.

406
00:35:15,469 --> 00:35:17,776
And you're the one
who sold them out last night.

407
00:35:17,983 --> 00:35:20,461
I don't know what you're talking about.

408
00:35:20,653 --> 00:35:21,995
I've never met Yana...

409
00:35:26,503 --> 00:35:27,654
Hey-hey-hey-hey.

410
00:35:27,749 --> 00:35:29,188
This is a Federal matter.

411
00:35:34,942 --> 00:35:38,491
Look at it. Look down the barrel.

412
00:35:38,682 --> 00:35:40,504
Tell me if you see the bullet.

413
00:35:40,696 --> 00:35:42,518
- Can you see it?
- I see it.

414
00:35:44,831 --> 00:35:46,642
He said he'll kill me.

415
00:35:46,738 --> 00:35:48,848
He said he'll kill my family.

416
00:35:48,944 --> 00:35:49,710
Who?

417
00:35:49,711 --> 00:35:51,054
Who said that?

418
00:35:51,150 --> 00:35:52,587
I don't know who!

419
00:35:52,588 --> 00:35:54,123
Who?

420
00:35:54,219 --> 00:35:57,671
I don't know who. He's with the Triads.

421
00:35:57,767 --> 00:35:59,110
He works forthe Changs.

422
00:35:59,205 --> 00:36:00,250
He knows where I live.

423
00:36:00,370 --> 00:36:02,658
He knows where my kids go to school.

424
00:36:08,412 --> 00:36:10,906
You stupid bastard.

425
00:36:11,002 --> 00:36:12,536
What do you think
Shiro Yanagawa's gonna do

426
00:36:12,632 --> 00:36:14,454
when he finds out you fucked him?

427
00:36:26,316 --> 00:36:28,648
Get a statement. Call the marshals.

428
00:36:28,744 --> 00:36:31,908
Put his family under protective custody.

429
00:36:32,100 --> 00:36:33,826
Down, down, down! Everyone down!

430
00:36:33,922 --> 00:36:35,265
A shooter on the! roof!

431
00:36:39,101 --> 00:36:39,964
Guys!

432
00:36:57,898 --> 00:36:59,228
This is Agent Wick.

433
00:36:59,348 --> 00:37:00,583
I need Chase Squad backup

434
00:37:00,679 --> 00:37:02,885
and an ambulance
to Sloan's Steakhouse. Now!

435
00:37:04,707 --> 00:37:06,050
Hang on, motherfucker.

436
00:38:02,249 --> 00:38:03,016
Nothing!

437
00:38:07,140 --> 00:38:08,386
This motherfucker's out.

438
00:38:24,498 --> 00:38:27,087
YAKUZA HEADQUARTERS
SAN FRANCISCO

439
00:38:27,183 --> 00:38:29,773
The Triads made us look like fools.

440
00:38:29,964 --> 00:38:33,225
Kill. Kill them.

441
00:38:33,321 --> 00:38:35,047
Give me the word...

442
00:38:35,143 --> 00:38:37,253
...and I'll make them disappear.

443
00:38:37,349 --> 00:38:39,938
Do it. Find them.

444
00:38:40,175 --> 00:38:43,679
I want all the heads
of every one of them.

445
00:38:43,966 --> 00:38:47,802
Nobody told me
you two were in charge now.

446
00:38:47,898 --> 00:38:49,912
Kira-san. Welcome home.

447
00:38:50,008 --> 00:38:52,310
Your presence honors us.

448
00:38:52,406 --> 00:38:56,913
And your stupidity insults my father.

449
00:38:57,105 --> 00:38:58,639
We were just discussing...

450
00:39:00,653 --> 00:39:03,530
I've brought word from Shiro directly.

451
00:39:03,626 --> 00:39:05,832
You are to do nothing
until he instructs you to.

452
00:39:06,064 --> 00:39:08,134
The Horses have been stolen!

453
00:39:08,230 --> 00:39:10,244
If we do not strike back...

454
00:39:13,025 --> 00:39:15,710
Are you disobeying my father?

455
00:39:20,985 --> 00:39:25,013
Good. I'd like a salad.

456
00:39:28,081 --> 00:39:31,150
I just got off a fourteen hour flight.

457
00:39:31,342 --> 00:39:33,548
I'd like a salad.

458
00:39:37,230 --> 00:39:39,110
Will somebody get me a salad?

459
00:39:39,386 --> 00:39:42,083
What? What kind?

460
00:39:46,211 --> 00:39:50,043
Chef. No blue cheese.

461
00:39:50,235 --> 00:39:52,820
No blue cheese.

462
00:39:52,940 --> 00:39:54,071
Takada...

463
00:40:06,730 --> 00:40:09,991
With dressing on the side, please.

464
00:40:11,869 --> 00:40:12,772
Hai.

465
00:40:15,170 --> 00:40:16,033
Bitch.

466
00:40:27,062 --> 00:40:27,925
Yeah.

467
00:40:28,308 --> 00:40:30,802
Special Agent Crawford.

468
00:40:30,898 --> 00:40:31,761
Who is this?

469
00:40:31,857 --> 00:40:33,175
A messenger.

470
00:40:33,295 --> 00:40:35,117
A messenger, huh?

471
00:40:35,309 --> 00:40:38,090
The police captain in the restaurant,
was he part of your message?

472
00:40:38,186 --> 00:40:39,529
He was a crooked cop.

473
00:40:39,721 --> 00:40:41,639
I just did what you want to do.

474
00:40:41,735 --> 00:40:44,420
What the hell do you know about
what I want, you fuck?

475
00:40:44,516 --> 00:40:47,009
I saw it in your eyes, John.

476
00:40:47,105 --> 00:40:49,215
Yeah, what did you see?

477
00:40:49,311 --> 00:40:53,051
Pain. Rage. Loneliness.

478
00:40:55,161 --> 00:40:56,886
I'll tell you what,

479
00:40:57,006 --> 00:40:59,093
why don't we meet at
my shrink's office and discuss it.

480
00:40:59,213 --> 00:41:01,323
You want the stolen shipment?

481
00:41:01,443 --> 00:41:04,464
Warehouse Sixteen. One hour.

482
00:41:14,054 --> 00:41:16,241
CHANG'S WAREHOUSE 16

483
00:41:23,171 --> 00:41:24,387
This is the FBI.

484
00:41:24,507 --> 00:41:27,097
Remain where you are and keep
your hands above your heads.

485
00:41:32,755 --> 00:41:34,961
What? Not happy to see us?

486
00:41:35,057 --> 00:41:36,975
This is private property.

487
00:41:37,071 --> 00:41:39,948
RSVP. We came to party, baby.

488
00:41:44,263 --> 00:41:48,867
Li Chang.
You still pretending to be legit?

489
00:41:49,058 --> 00:41:54,045
Watch your mouth.
You forget who you're talking to here.

490
00:41:58,017 --> 00:41:59,032
Open it.

491
00:42:02,197 --> 00:42:04,499
I said, open it.

492
00:42:05,937 --> 00:42:06,896
Open it!

493
00:42:20,706 --> 00:42:22,720
Put your hands
on the back of your head.

494
00:42:25,214 --> 00:42:26,940
Now, motherfucker.

495
00:42:31,789 --> 00:42:33,365
Get your fucking hands up.

496
00:42:42,476 --> 00:42:44,246
No weapons. He's clean.

497
00:42:47,943 --> 00:42:49,381
Victor Shaw.

498
00:42:50,340 --> 00:42:53,984
So that's what
you call yourself now huh?

499
00:42:54,176 --> 00:42:58,588
Hong Kong passport but
security license out of Tokyo. Fine.

500
00:42:59,956 --> 00:43:02,328
Check the warehouse.
Make sure nothing's hidden.

501
00:43:04,837 --> 00:43:07,099
It's you, isn't it?

502
00:43:07,219 --> 00:43:09,617
I remember your eyes.

503
00:43:09,737 --> 00:43:12,302
There's something
real familiar about them.

504
00:43:15,946 --> 00:43:18,919
It's the one thing the surgeons
can't change, can they?

505
00:43:19,111 --> 00:43:20,262
The eyes.

506
00:43:22,276 --> 00:43:25,824
They did a helluva job
on the rest of you, though.

507
00:43:25,944 --> 00:43:28,318
Wouldn't even know
you're the same man.

508
00:43:31,387 --> 00:43:35,510
But you are, aren't you?
I know you are.

509
00:43:41,792 --> 00:43:44,717
So what's the Yakuza hit man doing
working for the Triads?

510
00:43:48,745 --> 00:43:50,567
I know you understand me.

511
00:43:52,773 --> 00:43:54,787
It was you on the phone, wasn't it?

512
00:43:58,431 --> 00:44:00,316
What, don't remember?

513
00:44:00,436 --> 00:44:02,363
Maybe you remember my partner.

514
00:44:04,473 --> 00:44:06,007
You do, don't you?

515
00:44:07,734 --> 00:44:12,049
Remember his name? Tom Lone.

516
00:44:14,735 --> 00:44:16,653
Remember his wife, Diane?

517
00:44:18,187 --> 00:44:20,681
His four-year-old daughter, Amy?

518
00:44:20,872 --> 00:44:22,982
Remember a cabin in the woods.

519
00:44:24,213 --> 00:44:29,983
A cabin that you burned to the ground
with their bodies still inside?

520
00:44:30,271 --> 00:44:31,877
Remember that?

521
00:44:31,997 --> 00:44:33,723
Do you remember that?

522
00:44:35,354 --> 00:44:40,341
